## Building a Chat UI in React

**Mental model:** A scrollable list of `{ id, from, text }` messages plus a composer. Sending appends a user message and (here) a simulated reply. The one non-obvious piece is auto-scrolling to the newest message after each append — do it in an effect keyed on the message list, scrolling a bottom ref into view.

### Step 1 — Messages + draft
```jsx
const [messages, setMessages] = useState(seed);
const [draft, setDraft] = useState('');
```

### Step 2 — Send appends (immutably)
```jsx
const send = () => {
  const t = draft.trim();
  if (!t) return;
  setMessages((m) => [...m, { id: uid(), from: 'me', text: t }]);
  setDraft('');
  setTimeout(() => setMessages((m) => [...m, { id: uid(), from: 'them', text: `Echo: ${t}` }]), 600);
};
```

### Step 3 — Auto-scroll to bottom
```jsx
const endRef = useRef(null);
useEffect(() => { endRef.current?.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' }); }, [messages]);
```

### Step 4 — Bubble alignment by sender
```jsx
<div style={{ justifyContent: m.from === 'me' ? 'flex-end' : 'flex-start' }}>…</div>
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Empty send | Trim and ignore. |
| Scroll position | Auto-scroll only; respect user scroll-up in production. |
| Enter to send | Handle keydown on the input. |

**Interview tip:** The auto-scroll effect keyed on `messages` (scrolling a sentinel ref into view) is the detail that makes a chat feel right — and the production refinement is to *not* yank the view down if the user has scrolled up to read history.

