## Building a Chat UI in Vue 3

**Mental model:** A scrollable list of `{ id, from, text }` plus a composer. Sending appends a user message and a simulated reply. After each append, auto-scroll a bottom sentinel into view using `nextTick` (so the DOM has the new node before scrolling).

### Step 1 — Messages + draft
```js
const messages = ref(seed);
const draft = ref('');
const endRef = ref(null);
```

### Step 2 — Send appends
```js
function send() {
  const t = draft.value.trim();
  if (!t) return;
  messages.value.push({ id: uid(), from: 'me', text: t });
  draft.value = '';
  setTimeout(() => messages.value.push({ id: uid(), from: 'them', text: 'Echo: ' + t }), 600);
}
```

### Step 3 — Auto-scroll after DOM updates
```js
watch(messages, () => nextTick(() => endRef.value && endRef.value.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' })), { deep: true });
```

### Step 4 — Bubble alignment
```vue
<div :class="m.from === 'me' ? 'right' : 'left'">{{ m.text }}</div>
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Empty send | Trim and ignore. |
| Scroll timing | `nextTick` before scrolling. |
| Enter to send | `@keydown.enter`. |

**Interview tip:** `nextTick` is essential here — scrolling before Vue flushes the new message node into the DOM would scroll to the wrong place; that ordering is the Vue-specific gotcha.

