## Building a Chat UI in Angular

**Mental model:** A scrollable list of `{ id, from, text }` plus a composer. Sending appends a user message and a simulated reply. Auto-scroll the log to the bottom after each append using `@ViewChild` + `ngAfterViewChecked` (or a `setTimeout`). Classic `NgModule` setup, no `?.`/`??` (the build rejects them), no `FormsModule`.

### Step 1 — Messages + draft
```typescript
messages: Msg[] = [{ id: 'm0', from: 'them', text: 'Hey!' }];
draft = '';
@ViewChild('log') log!: ElementRef<HTMLElement>;
```

### Step 2 — Send appends
```typescript
send(): void {
  const t = this.draft.trim();
  if (!t) { return; }
  this.messages.push({ id: this.uid(), from: 'me', text: t });
  this.draft = '';
  setTimeout(() => this.messages.push({ id: this.uid(), from: 'them', text: 'Echo: ' + t }), 600);
}
```

### Step 3 — Auto-scroll to bottom
```typescript
ngAfterViewChecked(): void {
  const el = this.log.nativeElement;
  el.scrollTop = el.scrollHeight;
}
```

### Step 4 — Bubble alignment
```html
<div [class.me]="m.from === 'me'">{{ m.text }}</div>
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Empty send | Trim and ignore. |
| Scroll timing | `ngAfterViewChecked` runs post-render. |
| Enter to send | `(keydown.enter)`. |

**Interview tip:** Setting `scrollTop = scrollHeight` in `ngAfterViewChecked` guarantees the view is scrolled after Angular renders the new message — the lifecycle ordering is the key detail (production code would guard against forcing scroll when the user scrolled up).

